PLACEHOLDER — Ascended Barron: GroundTruth OS release signing key.

This file will hold the project's GPG PUBLIC key, used by ai-os-update to verify
that a downloaded release was genuinely signed by the project before installing
it (decisions Q5/Q52).

It is a PLACEHOLDER until the real release key is generated. While it says
PLACEHOLDER, ai-os-update skips the signature check (with a visible warning) so
that dev and pre-key installs still work. Once the real public key is dropped in
here (replacing this text with an ASCII-armored public key block), signature
verification becomes mandatory and a bad/missing signature is a hard failure.

To generate the key and produce this file, run, on the maintainer's machine:
    tools/generate-release-key.sh
(see that script; it never commits the PRIVATE key — only this public block).
